A man, simply identified as Oyakemeagbegha, has reportedly killed one Mr. Ebitein Enoch, who was deeply asleep in Ojobo Community, Burutu Local Government Area of Delta State. It was learnt that the incident occurred on Saturday evening after the suspect, now on the run, had a quarrel with the victim’s wife. It was also learnt that the suspect woke the victim up from his sleep and clubbed him to death with with a 2×2 polyne (wood). The Delta State Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe, did not pick phone calls or respond to a text message sent to him for confirmation.